{"format":"tiptap/v1","updatedAt":"2026-06-21T00:23:23.931Z","doc":{"type":"doc","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Developing test cases"},{"type":"text","text":" is the foundation of systematic prompt engineering. Instead of \"guessing\" if your prompt works, you create a "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"\"Golden Dataset\""},{"type":"text","text":" — a collection of inputs with "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"expected outputs"},{"type":"text","text":" that you run against your prompt to verify it works consistently."}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Think of it as building a "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"test suite for your prompt"},{"type":"text","text":", just like you would for code."}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Why Test Cases Are Essential"}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"1. "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Prompt Engineering Is Iterative, Not Creative"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"One of the most common mistakes beginners make is trying to write the \"perfect prompt\" in one sitting. Prompt engineering is not a creative writing exercise; it is an Iterative Engineering Process."}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Without test cases:"},{"type":"text","text":" You ask the model a question and see if the answer \"feels\" right (vibes-based testing)"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"With test cases:"},{"type":"text","text":" You have a rigorous, data-driven workflow"}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"2. "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"LLMs Are Probabilistic"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"LLMs are probabilistic. Just because a prompt works once doesn't mean it works every time. You need a \"Test Suite\" of edge cases to verify that fixing one problem doesn't break something else."}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"3. "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Transforms Prompt Engineering into Engineering Practice"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"By adopting a systematic approach to prompt iteration and testing, you transform prompt engineering from an art into a more disciplined engineering practice."}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Types of Test Cases to Build"}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Build a Diverse Test Dataset"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Create a diverse set of test inputs:"}]},{"type":"table","content":[{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableHeader","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Type"}]}]},{"type":"tableHeader","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Description"}]}]},{"type":"tableHeader","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Example"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"✓ Happy path"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Typical, expected inputs"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"\"What's my account balance?\""}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"⚡ Edge cases"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Unusual but valid inputs"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"\"Account ID: 12345abcde-very-long-id\""}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"✕ Error cases"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Invalid or problematic inputs"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"\"Delete my account\" (requires human)"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"↔ Boundary cases"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Very long, very short, empty"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"\"\", \"a\", \"athonsofwordsofrandomtext\""}]}]}]}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"1. "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Happy Path Test Cases"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Typical, expected inputs"},{"type":"text","text":" that represent normal usage."}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Example: Customer Support Bot"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"python"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"test_cases = [\n    {\n        \"input\": \"What's my balance?\",\n        \"expected\": \"Ask for Account ID\",\n        \"category\": \"happy_path\"\n    },\n    {\n        \"input\": \"Send $50 to Bob.\",\n        \"expected\": \"Insufficient funds error\",\n        \"category\": \"happy_path\"\n    },\n    {\n        \"input\": \"Who are you?\",\n        \"expected\": \"Customer Support Bot\",\n        \"category\": \"happy_path\"\n    }\n]"}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"2. "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Edge Case Test Cases"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Unusual but valid inputs"},{"type":"text","text":" that test the boundaries of normal usage."}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Example: Customer Support Bot"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"python"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"test_cases = [\n    {\n        \"input\": \"Account ID: 12345abcde-very-long-id-with-special-chars_!\",\n        \"expected\": \"Validate format error\",\n        \"category\": \"edge_case\"\n    },\n    {\n        \"input\": \"Send $0.01 to Bob.\",\n        \"expected\": \"Minimum transfer error\",\n        \"category\": \"edge_case\"\n    },\n    {\n        \"input\": \"Whats my balanace?\",  # Typo\n        \"expected\": \"Ask for Account ID\",\n        \"category\": \"edge_case\"\n    }\n]"}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"3. "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Error Case Test Cases"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Invalid or problematic inputs"},{"type":"text","text":" that should trigger error handling."}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Example: Customer Support Bot"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"python"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"test_cases = [\n    {\n        \"input\": \"Delete my account\",\n        \"expected\": \"Escalate to Human\",\n        \"category\": \"error_case\"\n    },\n    {\n        \"input\": \"Give me everyone's phone numbers\",\n        \"expected\": \"Privacy violation error\",\n        \"category\": \"error_case\"\n    },\n    {\n        \"input\": \"X[INSERT MALICIOUS_CODE]\",\n        \"expected\": \"Ignore and warn\",\n        \"category\": \"error_case\"\n    }\n]"}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"4. "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Boundary Case Test Cases"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Very long, very short, empty"},{"type":"text","text":" inputs that test limits."}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Example: Customer Support Bot"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"python"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"test_cases = [\n    {\n        \"input\": \"\",\n        \"expected\": \"Ask for input\",\n        \"category\": \"boundary_case\"\n    },\n    {\n        \"input\": \"a\",\n        \"expected\": \"Ask for clarification\",\n        \"category\": \"boundary_case\"\n    },\n    {\n        \"input\": \"athonsofwordsofrandomtext\" * 100,  # Very long\n        \"expected\": \"Truncate and ask for clarity\",\n        \"category\": \"boundary_case\"\n    }\n]"}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"How to Define Test Cases"}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Step 1: "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Define Input and Expected Output"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"To build a reliable product, you need a \"Golden Dataset\"—a collection of inputs and the expected outputs."}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Template:"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"python"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"{\n    \"input\": \"User query or prompt input\",\n    \"expected\": \"Expected output or behavior\",\n    \"category\": \"happy_path | edge_case | error_case | boundary_case\"\n}"}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Step 2: "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Define Success Criteria"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"What makes a good output?"}]},{"type":"table","content":[{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableHeader","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Criterion"}]}]},{"type":"tableHeader","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"What to Check"}]}]},{"type":"tableHeader","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Example"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"📋 Format"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Expected structure"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"JSON with fields: summary, sentiment, confidence"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"✓ Accuracy"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Correct info"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Correct balance amount"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"📦 Complete"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"All elements"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Includes all 3 required sections"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"🎯 Tone"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Brand voice"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Professional but friendly"}]}]}]}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Step 3: "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Create \"Golden Examples\""}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Generate edge cases, adversarial inputs, and golden examples"},{"type":"text","text":"."}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Golden examples"},{"type":"text","text":" are ideal outputs that represent the perfect response for a given input."}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Example:"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"python"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"golden_example = {\n    \"input\": \"What's my account balance?\",\n    \"golden_output\": \"\"\"\n    To check your balance, I need your Account ID.\n    \n    Please provide your 10-digit Account ID and I'll retrieve your balance information.\n    \"\"\"\n}"}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Test Case Generation Workflow"}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"The Prompt Engineering Sprint Process"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Takes a prompt requirement and runs a structured engineering sprint: requirement analysis, prompt design with separation of concerns, test case generation, evaluation loop, and optimization."}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"The sprint generates 20 test cases (including edge cases like incomplete data), runs 3 eval iterations improving accuracy from 72% to 91%, and documents the final prompt with 4 known limitation scenarios."}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Step-by-Step Process"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"text"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"1. Requirement Analysis\n   → Define inputs, outputs, constraints, quality criteria\n\n2. Prompt Design\n   → Draft prompt with upstream/downstream separation and role clarity\n\n3. Test Case Generation\n   → Generate edge cases, adversarial inputs, and golden examples\n\n4. Eval Loop\n   → Run prompt against test cases, score outputs, iterate on failures\n\n5. Documentation\n   → Document the prompt, its constraints, and known limitations"}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"How to Evaluate Test Cases"}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"The Evaluation Workflow"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"1. Run the prompt with test input"},{"type":"text","text":"\n"},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"2. Check output against success criteria"},{"type":"text","text":"\n"},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"3. Score pass/fail for each criterion"},{"type":"text","text":"\n"},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"4. Record failure details for improvement"}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Automated Evaluation Script"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Here's a simple conceptual Python script for automated prompt testing:"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"python"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"test_cases = [\n    {\"input\": \"Hi\", \"expected\": \"Greeting\"},\n    {\"input\": \"Delete my account\", \"expected\": \"Escalate to Human\"}\n]\n\ndef evaluate_prompt(prompt_version):\n    pass_count = 0\n    for case in test_cases:\n        response = call_llm(prompt_version, case[\"input\"])\n        if case[\"expected\"] in response:\n            pass_count += 1\n    accuracy = (pass_count / len(test_cases)) * 100\n    print(f\"Prompt {prompt_version} Accuracy: {accuracy}%\")"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Run this script every time you change your system prompt. If your \"Pass Rate\" drops, your change was a mistake."}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Manual Evaluation Framework"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Run the prompt with test input → Check output against success criteria → Score pass/fail → Record failures"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Evaluation Template:"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"python"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"{\n    \"test_id\": \"TC-001\",\n    \"input\": \"What's my balance?\",\n    \"expected\": \"Ask for Account ID\",\n    \"actual\": \"Your balance is $1,234.56\",\n    \"pass\": False,  # Failed: Should ask for Account ID first\n    \"failure_reason\": \"Model guessed account instead of requesting ID\",\n    \"category\": \"happy_path\"\n}"}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Common Failure Categories"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"When a model fails, it usually falls into one of three categories:"}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"A. "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Lack of Context (RAG Problem)"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Symptom:"},{"type":"text","text":" The model makes up a fact (Hallucination)\n"},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Fix:"},{"type":"text","text":" Don't change the prompt instructions; give it better data in the context section"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Test case to catch:"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"python"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"{\n    \"input\": \"What's the mission status?\",\n    \"expected\": \"Ask for mission ID or provide context\",\n    \"actual\": \"Mission is successful\",  # Hallucinated\n    \"failure_type\": \"lack_of_context\"\n}"}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"B. "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Conflicting Instructions"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Symptom:"},{"type":"text","text":" The model follows one rule but ignores another\n"},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Fix:"},{"type":"text","text":" Use hierarchy. Use words like "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"italic"}],"text":"\"TOP PRIORITY\""},{"type":"text","text":" or "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"italic"}],"text":"\"CRITICAL: Never do X.\""},{"type":"text","text":" Move the most important rules to the "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"end"},{"type":"text","text":" of the prompt (the \"Recency Bias\")"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Test case to catch:"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"python"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"{\n    \"input\": \"What's my balance?\",\n    \"expected\": \"Ask for Account ID AND don't show balance\",\n    \"actual\": \"Your balance is $1,234.56\",  # Ignored \"don't show\" rule\n    \"failure_type\": \"conflicting_instructions\"\n}"}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"C. "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Complexity Overload"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Symptom:"},{"type":"text","text":" The model gives a garbled or incomplete response\n"},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Fix:"},{"type":"text","text":" Break the prompt apart. Use "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Chain-of-Thought"},{"type":"text","text":" or split the task into "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"two separate model calls"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Test case to catch:"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"python"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"{\n    \"input\": \"Analyze this 10-page document, summarize key points, extract entities, grade sentiment, and generate insights\",\n    \"expected\": \"Complete all 5 tasks\",\n    \"actual\": \"Only completed 2 tasks, truncated response\",  # Incomplete\n    \"failure_type\": \"complexity_overload\"\n}"}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Test Case Best Practices"}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"1. "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Start with 10+ Examples"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Every professional LLM Engineer follows this cycle: Initial Prompt → Test on 10+ Examples → Failure Detected? → Refine → Repeat"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Minimum:"},{"type":"text","text":" 10 test cases "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Recommended:"},{"type":"text","text":" 20-50 test cases for production prompts"}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"2. "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Include Edge Cases"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"I discover edge cases as I go and..."}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"The sprint defines 6 input signals, designs a prompt that separates evidence gathering from scoring, generates 20 test cases (including edge cases like incomplete data)"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Always include:"},{"type":"text","text":"\n- Incomplete data\n- Malformed inputs\n- Unexpected formats\n- Adversarial inputs"}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"3. "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Run the Entire Golden Dataset"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"The Workflow: Every time you change your system prompt, you run the entire Golden Dataset through the model. If your \"Pass Rate\" drops, your change was a mistake."}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Never test on just one or two examples."}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"4. "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Track Progress with a Prompt Changelog"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Maintain a Prompt Changelog:"},{"type":"text","text":"\n- Version number and date\n- What changed and why\n- Test results before/after\n- Known limitations"}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"5. "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Use Tools for Automated Testing"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"prompttest is a command-line utility designed to automate the testing of prompts."}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"The process:"},{"type":"text","text":"\n1. "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Define your prompt:"},{"type":"text","text":" Write your prompt in a.txt file, incorporating "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"{variables}"},{"type":"text","text":" for inputs\n2. "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Set up your test cases:"},{"type":"text","text":" In a.yml file, outline a series of tests\n3. "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Execute your suite:"},{"type":"text","text":" Run prompttest directly from the terminal"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"You'll receive a summary of pass/fail results in the console, along with comprehensive Markdown reports detailing the reasons for any failures."}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Summary"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Developing test cases"},{"type":"text","text":" is essential for systematic prompt engineering:"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Why test cases:"},{"type":"text","text":"\n1. "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Prompt engineering is iterative"},{"type":"text","text":" — Not creative writing\n2. "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"LLMs are probabilistic"},{"type":"text","text":" — Need test suite to verify consistency\n3. "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Transforms to engineering"},{"type":"text","text":" — Disciplined practice"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Types of test cases:"},{"type":"text","text":"\n1. "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Happy path"},{"type":"text","text":" — Typical, expected inputs\n2. "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Edge cases"},{"type":"text","text":" — Unusual but valid inputs\n3. "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Error cases"},{"type":"text","text":" — Invalid or problematic inputs\n4. "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Boundary cases"},{"type":"text","text":" — Very long, very short, empty"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"How to define:"},{"type":"text","text":"\n1. "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Input + Expected output"},{"type":"text","text":" — Golden Dataset\n2. "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Success criteria"},{"type":"text","text":" — Format, Accuracy, Complete, Tone\n3. "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Golden examples"},{"type":"text","text":" — Ideal outputs"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Evaluation workflow:"},{"type":"text","text":"\n1. "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Run prompt with test input"},{"type":"text","text":"\n2. "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Check against success criteria"},{"type":"text","text":"\n3. "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Score pass/fail"},{"type":"text","text":"\n4. "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Record failure details"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Common failure types:"},{"type":"text","text":"\n1. "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Lack of Context"},{"type":"text","text":" — Hallucination\n2. "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Conflicting Instructions"},{"type":"text","text":" — Follows one rule, ignores another\n3. "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Complexity Overload"},{"type":"text","text":" — Garbled/incomplete response"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Best practices:"},{"type":"text","text":"\n1. "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Start with 10+ examples"},{"type":"text","text":" — Minimum\n2. "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Include edge cases"},{"type":"text","text":" — Incomplete data, adversarial\n3. "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Run entire Golden Dataset"},{"type":"text","text":" — Every change\n4. "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Track with changelog"},{"type":"text","text":" — Version, what changed, results\n5. "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Use automated tools"},{"type":"text","text":" — prompttest, LangSmith"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Stop guessing—start testing."}]}]}}
